article.headline: SC-Upstate 68, Kennesaw State 53
article.story: SPARTANSBURG, S.C. -- Torrey Craig scored 28 points and grabbed 10 rebounds to lead South Carolina-Upstate past Kennesaw State 68-53 on Saturday. Craig was 10 of 12 from the field, 5 of 7 from 3-point range and 3 of 4 from the charity stripe. SC-Upstate (9-7, 3-1 Atlantic Sun Conference) jumped out to an early 10-2 lead behind five points from Craig. The Spartans would push that lead to 15, 30-15, after a 3-pointer from Craig and took a 37-21 lead into halftime. SC-Upstate led by at least eight points throughout the second half. The Spartans shot 49.1 percent (26 of 53) from the field compared to just 37 percent (20 of 54) for Kennesaw State. The Owls (3-13, 0-5) only made three of their 17 3-point attempts. SC-Upstate forced 16 turnovers and scored 23 points off those errors. Aaron Anderson led Kennesaw State with 15 points and 11 rebounds.
